I think that while serialization still is not done, it's important we have good field names to avoid inconsistency and future re-work.

One thing that I have thought is use the same naming for synapses parameters which are specified in `SpatialPooler`, `TemporalMemory`, and `TP*`.

In `SpatialPooler`, we have:

```
synPermInactiveDec
synPermActiveInc
synPermBelowStimulusInc
synPermConnected
```

In `TemporalMemory`:

```
initialPermanence
connectedPermanence
permanenceIncrement
permanenceDecrement
```

And finally `Cells4`:

```
permInitial
ermConnected
permMax
permDec
permInc
```

My proposal is we have a single file called `SynapsesParameters.capnp` to centralize all generic synapses parameters. 

```
struct SynapsesParametersProto {
  synapseInitialPermanence @1 :Float32;
  synapseConnectedPermanence @2 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceIncrement @3 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceDecrement @4 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceMin @5 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceMax @6 :Float32;
}
```

Another option is we put these field names into existent `ConnectionsProto` (which could be even better):

```
struct ConnectionsProto {

  # Next ID: 3
  struct SynapseProto {
    presynapticCell @0 :UInt32;
    permanence @1 :Float32;
    destroyed @2 :Bool;
  }

  # Next ID: 3
  struct SegmentProto {
    synapses @0 :List(SynapseProto);
    destroyed @1 :Bool;
    lastUsedIteration @2 :UInt64;
  }

  # Next ID: 1
  struct CellProto {
    segments @0 :List(SegmentProto);
  }

  synapseInitialPermanence @1 :Float32;
  synapseConnectedPermanence @2 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceIncrement @3 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceDecrement @4 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceMin @5 :Float32;
  synapsePermanenceMax @6 :Float32;

  cells @7 :List(CellProto);
  maxSegmentsPerCell @8 :UInt8;
  iteration @9 :UInt64;
}
```

